During the course, the students discuss the research problem, theoretic and methodological framework, methods of data collection and conclusions with their co-learners under supervision, and practice public defending of the Master's thesis in the pre-defence process.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aims of the course are: - to support the students in the process of preparing the Master's thesis, using feedback by teachers and co-learners, reviewing parts of the thesis and public discussions; - to develop the proficiency at working with scientific literature and academic writing; - to prepare for the public presentation of the thesis.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course, the student: - is able to work with scientific literature and review the relevant theoretical views in the first version of the thesis; - is able to justify the choices made and views presented in all parts of the thesis; - is ready to submit the first version the thesis and defend it in public; - is able to critically analyse the parts of theses of co-learners and the Master's thesis submitted for pre-defence, and to provide supportive oral and written feedback.
